Interface DatumTransformation

BaseDatumTransformation
public interface DatumTransformation
extends GeodeticObject, PEObject, NamedObject

Represents a datum transformation from a source datum to a target datum.

forward

public void forward(Point3D point)
             throws CalculationException
Transforms a point in the source datum having longitude (x) in radians, latitude (y) in radians, and ellipsoidal height (z) in meters to the equivalent coordinates in the target datum.

Parameters:
point - a point having x (longitude), y (latitude), and z (ellipsoidal height) components. This value will be altered within the method. The resulting value will be in reference to the target datum. Latitude and longitude are always in radians.
CalculationException

             throws CalculationException
Transforms a point in the target datum having longitude (x) in radians, latitude (y) in radians, and ellipsoidal height (z) in meters to the equivalent coordinates in the source datum.

Parameters:
point - a point having x (longitude), y (latitude), and z (ellipsoidal height) components. This value will be altered within the method. The resulting value will be in reference to the source datum. Latitude and longitude are always in radians.
